    <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">A collection of declarations and correspondence attributed to the Fatimid Caliph al-Ḥākim bi-Amr Allāh.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Title from heading of first report (f. 1v).</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="505" ind1="0" ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">1. f. 1v-8r: Nuskhat al-sijill alladhī wujida muʻallaqan ʻalá al-mashāhid fī ghaybat Mawlānā al-Imām al-Ḥākim -- 2. f. 8r-9v: al-Sijill al-manhī fīhi ʻan al-khamr -- 3. f. 9v-18r: Khabar al-Yahūd wa-al-Naṣārī -- 4. f. 18r: Nuskhat mā katabahu al-Qirmaṭī ilá Mawlana al-Ḥākim bi-Amr Allāh Amīr al-Muʼminīn ʻinda wuṣūlihi ilá Miṣr -- 5. f. 18v: Fa-ajābahu salāmuhu ʻalaynā -- 6. f. 19r-19v: Mīthāq walī al-zamān -- 7. f. 19v-33v : al-Kitāb al-maʻrūf bi-al-Naqḍ al-khafī -- 8. f. 33v-38r: al-Risālah al-mawsūmah bi-badw al-tawḥīd li-daʻwat al-Ḥaqq -- 9. f. 38r-41v : Mīthāq al-nisāʼ -- 10. f. 41v-50v : Risālat al-balāgh wa-al-nihāyah fī al-tawḥīd -- 11. f. 50v-62r : al-Ghāyah wa-al-naṣīḥah -- 12. f. 62r-74r : Kitāb fīhi ḥaqāʼiq mā yaẓhar -- 13. f. 74r-90v : al-Sīrah al-mustaqīmah -- 14. f. 91r-105v : al-Mawsūmah bi-Kashf al-Ḥaqāʼiq -- 15. f. 105v-118r : al-Risalah al-mawsūmah bi-sabab al-asbāb wa-al-kanz li-man ayqana wa-istajāb.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="546" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Arabic.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Foliation: Modern foliation added in pencil, upper left recto; catchwords every verso, lower left.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Layout: 14-15 long lines; border-ruled; one poem is set in two columns.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Script: Naskh in black ink; pointed, fully vocalized. Headers in thuluth.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Decoration: Textblock border-ruled in red. Rubrications in red and green. Headers in red or yellow ink often on cloudbands with yellow, green, and black fill; some headers have more elaborate illumination in yellow and red (f. 18r, for example). Red roundels punctuate the text.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Shelfmark: MS Or 120.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="541" ind1="1" ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Gift of David Eugene Smith, 1931-1934.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="563" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Brown leather with blind stamped central medallion and blind tooled frame. Marbled paper pastedowns.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Origin: Copy is undated, though perhaps copied in the 16th century. There is a note written across the spine lining with the date 864 A.H. (1460), though that date may be unrelated to this copy.</subfield>
    </datafield>
